Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon compendium of
Puck=E2=80=99s best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Matt Belloni bestows his annual =E2=80=9Cawards season awar=
ds=E2=80=9D honoring the biggest imbroglios, unambiguous villains, and jarr=
ing subplots in the death march to Oscars night. Indeed, from the contender=
s who were never really contenders, to Sean Baker=E2=80=99s not-so-subtle N=
etflix-bashing at the dais, one of the oddest and most
roller-coastery seasons in memory deserves its own set of accolades=E2=80=
=A6

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Julia Ioffe reveals the whispered frustrations among =
Zelensky supporters following his Oval Office thrashing. Lauren Sherman cha=
rts the fashion industry=E2=80=99s response to Bally designer Simone Bellot=
ti=E2=80=99s forthcoming departure to
